# user.sdkconfig — optional build overrides for your board.
#
# Copy this file to user.sdkconfig and uncomment the settings you want.
# This file is appended last to the build configuration, so it overrides
# all board defaults. Run a full clean (fullclean.sh) after changing it.
#
# ─── Partition table (EPDIY_V7 and other 8 MiB ESP32-S3 boards) ─────────────
#
# The app partition holds the compiled firmware (including any fonts you add
# with add_font.py). The remaining flash is available as a MicroPython
# filesystem for your .py scripts and data files.
#
# Pick ONE layout and uncomment it:

# More app space (3 MiB) — default; fits larger firmware builds; ~5 MiB for .py files
# CONFIG_PARTITION_TABLE_CUSTOM_FILENAME="partitions-8MiB-large-app.csv"

# More filesystem space (2 MiB app) — smaller firmware only; ~6 MiB for .py files
# CONFIG_PARTITION_TABLE_CUSTOM_FILENAME="partitions-8MiB-large-fs.csv"

# ─── Partition table (LILYGO_T5_47 and other 16 MiB boards) ─────────────────
#
# Pick ONE layout and uncomment it:

# More app space (4 MiB) — fits many compiled-in fonts; ~12 MiB for .py files
# CONFIG_PARTITION_TABLE_CUSTOM_FILENAME="partitions-16MiB-large-app.csv"

# More filesystem space (2 MiB app) — fewer compiled fonts; ~14 MiB for .py files
# CONFIG_PARTITION_TABLE_CUSTOM_FILENAME="partitions-16MiB-large-fs.csv"

# ─── Partition table (32 MiB boards) ─────────────────────────────────────────
#
# No 32 MiB partition table is shipped out of the box. To add one, create a
# new file (e.g. partitions-32MiB-large-app.csv) in
# micropython/ports/esp32/ following the same layout as the existing tables,
# then reference it here and add a matching entry to the patch file
# (patches/micropython/001-add-board-type.patch) so it survives a clean
# submodule reset.  Also set the flash-size keys to match:
#
# CONFIG_ESPTOOLPY_FLASHSIZE_16MB=
# CONFIG_ESPTOOLPY_FLASHSIZE_32MB=y
# CONFIG_ESPTOOLPY_FLASHSIZE="32MB"
# CONFIG_PARTITION_TABLE_CUSTOM_FILENAME="partitions-32MiB-large-app.csv"
